  "issue_title": "[Bug] `MirrorClient` is synchronous but called from async validator forward path \u2014 blocks the event loop",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\n`gittensor/utils/mirror/client.py` builds requests with the synchronous `requests` library. `mirror_scan.py` and other call sites are reached from `gittensor/validator/forward.py`, which is `async def`. Each blocking `requests.post(...)` ties up the event loop for the full RTT (often hundreds of ms for cold cache misses, seconds under cloudflare-throttle), starving:\n\n- Heartbeats to bittensor's metagraph subscription.\n- `bt.logging` flush callbacks.\n- Any concurrent dendrite calls.\n\nThe validator's apparent latency to other subnet participants spikes\nduring mirror calls.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Run `gittensor/validator/forward.py` with `bt.logging.set_trace()`\n   and watch the event-loop latency between log flushes.\n2. Trigger a fresh-cache mirror call (`MirrorClient.fetch(...)`).\n3. Observe a multi-second gap between log lines while the mirror\n   call completes.\n4. Confirm with `asyncio.get_event_loop().slow_callback_duration = 0.1`\n   that the mirror call appears as a slow callback.\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nEither:\n- Wrap mirror calls in `asyncio.to_thread(...)` so the blocking I/O\n  happens on a thread pool.\n- Migrate `MirrorClient` to `httpx.AsyncClient` and await each call.\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\nSynchronous I/O in async context; event loop stalls for the full\nmirror response time.\n\n## Additional Context\n\n- Related: PR #687 / IS #696 (HTTP connection pooling for issue   discovery) \u2014 mostly about pooling, not async-ness. This is the   orthogonal `event-loop-blocking` issue.\n- Suggested fix: `from asyncio import to_thread; resp = await   to_thread(self.session.post, url, ...)`.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-07T17:45:31.000Z",
